This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with building detection from satellite multispectral imagery data using deep learning techniques. Additionally, the use of U-Net, a popular convolutional neural network architecture for image segmentation, further supports this categorization. The paper also involves data preprocessing and data preparation, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of OpenStreetMap data suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on improving accuracy through modifications to the deep learning approach suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
